Dozens of people have been arrested amid riots in Pakistan that stemmed from blasphemy accusations against a Hindu school principal. Authorities said rioters attacked a private school and a Hindu temple in Ghokti, about 260 miles northeast of Karachi, on Sunday,UPI report. “In the temple, they broke windows, and the things inside, including our idols, were also damaged,” Mukhi Kika Ram, leader of the local Hindu community, told Al Jazeera.